HEADWORD: Hanger-on
<hw>Hang"er-on`</hw> <pr>(-⟦ocr⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Hangers-on</plw>
<pr>(-⟦etil⟧rz-⟦ocr⟧n`)</pr>.</plu> <def>One who hangs on, or sticks to,
a person, place, or service; a dependent; one who adheres to others'
society longer than he is wanted.</def> <rj><au>Goldsmith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

